Jobsphere - Job Portal

📌 Project Overview

Jobsphere is a full-stack job portal that connects job seekers and employers, streamlining the recruitment process. The platform features role-based access for Jobseekers, Employers, and Admins, ensuring smooth operations, secure user authentication, and an efficient hiring experience.

🚀 Features

🏆 Jobseekers

Register and create a profile with education and experience details.

Browse and apply for job postings.

Receive real-time employer response updates (Shortlisted, Pending, Rejected).

🏢 Employers

Register and create a company profile.

Post job openings with detailed descriptions and requirements.

View and manage job applications.

Shortlist, reject, or accept applications.

🔧 Admin

Monitor platform activity and manage employer accounts.

Remove inactive or fraudulent employers.

Maintain system security and oversee user authentication.

🛠️ Technologies Used

🎨 Frontend

React.js - UI Framework

Tailwind CSS - Styling

⚙️ Backend

Node.js - Server Runtime

Express.js - Web Server Framework

🗄️ Database

MongoDB - NoSQL Database

📦 Containerization

Docker - For deployment and containerized application management

🔍 Other Tools & Libraries

Multer - For file uploads

JWT - Secure authentication using JSON Web Token

🏗️ Getting Started

Clone the Repository

git clone git@github.com:vigneshjraju/Project-Jobportal.git
cd jobsphere

Install Dependencies

npm install

Run the Application

Development Mode

npm run dev

Docker Setup

Ensure Docker is installed, then build and run the project:

docker compose up --build

Accessing the Application

Once the container starts, the application will be available at:

http://localhost:5000

📹 Demo Video : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0l6fz_0lRuM


